# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .gitignore for the public OTA-mirror repo (monerousd/ota-mirror)
#
# This file is the security perimeter for the public OTA-distribution
# repo. It must be PERMISSIVE — i.e. block everything by default and
# allowlist exactly the build artifacts the wallet's electron-updater
# needs to fetch. A leaked seed / PAT / SSH key / wallet keys file
# pushed to a public GitHub repo is a permanent leak — git history
# survives even after deletion, and bots scrape new commits in real
# time looking for credentials.
#
# The pattern: deny everything (`*`), then explicitly un-ignore the
# narrow set of files we know are safe. New file types added later
# require a PR that updates this file.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Default-deny — the protected stance.
*

# Allow only the OTA-mirror artifacts:

# electron-updater manifests (tiny YAML)
!latest-mac.yml
!latest.yml
!latest-linux.yml

# Mac installer artifacts
!Monero USD Wallet*.dmg
!Monero USD Wallet*.zip

# Windows installer artifacts
!Monero USD Wallet Setup*.exe

# Linux installer artifacts
!Monero USD Wallet*.AppImage
!monerousd-desktop_*.deb

# Differential-update blockmaps (tiny binary, alongside each artifact)
!*.blockmap

# README + this gitignore so the repo isn't featureless
!.gitignore
!README.md

# GitHub Pages custom-domain marker — REQUIRED for the wallet's
# OTA endpoint to resolve at update.monerousd.org instead of the
# default <user>.github.io URL. Single-line file containing the
# bare hostname.
!CNAME

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Explicit deny-list for high-risk file extensions (defense in depth —
# the leading `*` already covers these, but listing explicitly makes
# the intent unambiguous to a reader).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Wallet seeds, keys, recovery phrases
*.seed
*.keys
*.wallet
*.wallet.json
*.address.txt
*.spend_key
*.view_key
mnemonic*
seed*
recovery*

# SSH / SSL / signing keys
id_rsa
id_ed25519
id_ecdsa
id_dsa
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
*.p12
*.pfx
*.gpg
*.asc

# Cryptocurrency wallet files (any chain)
wallet.dat
*.wallet.dat
keystore*.json
UTC--*

# Environment / config files that commonly hold secrets
.env
.env.*
*.envrc
.envrc
secrets.json
secrets.yml
secrets.yaml
credentials.json
credentials.yml
config.local.*
*.secret

# Auth tokens / API keys
*.token
*.pat
*.api_key
.npmrc
.netrc

# Personal config dirs sometimes copied by mistake
.aws/
.ssh/
.gnupg/
.monerousd/
.config/
.docker/

# Dev artifacts — should never be in an OTA repo anyway
node_modules/
dist/
build/
out/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.log
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
.cache/

# Database files (backend state, local indexer state, etc.)
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.db-shm
*.db-wal

# Claude / agent state
.claude/
.cursor/

# Source code (this is an OTA-MIRROR repo, never source)
*.js
*.ts
*.cjs
*.mjs
*.cpp
*.h
*.rs
*.go
*.py
*.sh
*.bash
src/
backend/
frontend/
tests/

# Docs that shouldn't be on the OTA mirror
*.md
!README.md
